org.sbml.squeezer

Class UnitFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.squeezer.UnitFactory

  • public class UnitFactory
extends Object
    A factory class that creates frequently used instances of Unit and UnitDefinition if these are not yet present in a Model. To this end, it always checks the Model and tries to obtain existing UnitDefinitions from the Model whenever this is possible. (2010-10-22)
    Author:
    Andreas Dräger

      • checkUnitDefinitions

        public static final org.sbml.jsbml.UnitDefinition checkUnitDefinitions(org.sbml.jsbml.UnitDefinition unitdef,
                                                                       org.sbml.jsbml.Model model)
        Avoids adding identical unit definitions multiple times to the model.
        Parameters:
        unitdef - a unit definition that should be added to the given model.
        model - the model that is to be tested if it really lacks the given unit definition.
        Returns:
        the unit definition found in the model or the given unit definition that was added to the model if lacking.
